                                <comments>
                            <comment id="17217266" author="ajisakaa" created="Tue, 20 Oct 2020 04:56:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I found this while writing a patch for &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HADOOP-17175&quot; title=&quot;[JDK11] Fix javadoc errors in hadoop-common module&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HADOOP-17175&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HADOOP-17175&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17217276" author="ayushtkn" created="Tue, 20 Oct 2020 05:19:02 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanx &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=aajisaka&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;aajisaka&quot;&gt;aajisaka&lt;/a&gt; for fixing, This got in post my change, I had doubts that old PR&apos;s might get merged with normal guava classes. Do you think we can add some enforcer rules, to prevent addition of &lt;tt&gt;com.google.common&lt;/tt&gt; imports? That would be good, if there is a way to do so.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17217373" author="ajisakaa" created="Tue, 20 Oct 2020 07:10:08 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;Do you think we can add some enforcer rules, to prevent addition of com.google.common imports?&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Yes, we can add some enforce rules. I&apos;ll update the PR.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17217954" author="ahussein" created="Tue, 20 Oct 2020 21:38:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hey &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=aajisaka&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;aajisaka&quot;&gt;aajisaka&lt;/a&gt;, thanks for working on this patch.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The guava enforcer rules were introduced to warn against increasing the reliance on guava classes; specifically to prevent the new patches from re-introducing code that was already &quot;un-guaved&quot;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-xml&quot;&gt;
          &amp;lt;property name=&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;illegalClasses&quot;&lt;/span&gt;
            value=&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;^com\.google\.common\.base\.(Optional|Function|Predicate|Supplier), ^com\.google\.common\.collect\.(ImmutableListMultimap)&quot;&lt;/span&gt;/&amp;gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;After merging that patch, the rules are only checking for imports that start with com.google. By Introducing shading, the regex becomes obsolete because the packages have a different prefix &lt;tt&gt;org.apache.hadoop.thirdparty.*&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;br/&gt;
I suggested that rules are modified to make sure that those guava classes are not used in Hadoop code.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17218153" author="ajisakaa" created="Wed, 21 Oct 2020 07:25:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=ahussein&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;ahussein&quot;&gt;ahussein&lt;/a&gt; for your comment. I&apos;ll create an additional PR.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17218157" author="ajisakaa" created="Wed, 21 Oct 2020 07:36:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Filed &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HADOOP-17319&quot; title=&quot;Update the checkstyle config to ban some guava functions&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HADOOP-17319&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HADOOP-17319&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; to update the config&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
